    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 26</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-19-2" n="19" prev="ADub.III.73.002.025.trl.xml#line-19-1" />
                        <l n="1">And you shall make the tabernacle
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            with ten curtains of twined linen, and blue and purple
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and scarlet silk, with cherubim — you shall make them of embroiderer’s
                            work.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="128v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="2">The length of one curtain twenty-eight
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four cubits:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            all the curtains shall have the same measure.</l>
                        <l n="3">The five curtains shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            coupled together, one to another, and the other five curtains shall be coupled
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            one to another.</l>
                        <l n="4">And you shall make loops of blue
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            on the edge of the one outmost curtain in the place of coupling, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            you shall do so in the edge of the second outmost curtain in the place
                            of coupling.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="5">You shall make fifty loops in the one curtain,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and you shall make fifty loops in the edge of the second curtain
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            in the place of coupling, loops opposite one
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            another.</l>
                        <l n="6">And you shall make fifty hooks of gold,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            and couple the curtains together with the hooks.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            And the tabernacle shall be one.</l>
                        <l n="7">And you shall make curtains
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            of goats’ hair for a tent over the tabernacle.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            You shall make eleven curtains.</l>
                        <l n="8">The length of one
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            curtain thirty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four cubits:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            one measure for eleven curtains.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="9">And you shall couple five curtains separately and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            six curtains separately, and you shall double over the sixth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            curtain in the front of the tabernacle.</l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            And you shall make fifty loops on the edge of the one outmost curtain
                            <milestone unit="page" n="129r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            in the place of coupling and fifty loops in the edge
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            of the second curtain in the place of coupling.</l>
                        <l n="11">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            And you shall make fifty hooks of bronze, and put the hooks
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            into the loops, and couple the tent together. And it shall be
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            one.</l>
                        <l n="12">And the surplus that remains additionally of the curtains
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            of the tent: you shall hang the half of the curtain that remains in surplus
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            over the back of the tabernacle.</l>
                        <l n="13">And the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            cubit on the one side and the cubit on the other side of that which remains
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            in the length of the curtains of the tent shall be hung over the sides
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            of the tabernacle on this side and on this side, to cover
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            it.</l>
                        <l n="14">And you shall make a covering for the tent of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            rams’ skins dyed red, and a <addSpan spanTo="#add001"
                                 /><emph>covering</emph><anchor xml:id="add001" /> of porpoise skins
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            above.</l>
                        <l n="15">And you shall make boards
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            for the tabernacle of acacia wood, standing:</l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            Ten cubits the length of a board, and a cubit and a half
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            the breadth of one board.</l>
                        <l n="17">Two
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            tenons shall there be in one board that fit together:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            thus shall you do for all the boards of the tabernacle.</l>
                        <l n="18">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            And you shall make the boards for the tabernacle, twenty boards
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            on the south side southward.</l>
                        <l n="19">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            you shall make forty bases of silver under the twenty boards,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="129v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            two bases under one board for its two tenons, and two bases
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            under one board for its two tenons.</l>
                        <l n="20">And for the <supplied reason="lost">second</supplied> side
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            of the tabernacle on the north side: twenty boards.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="21">And their forty bases of silver, two bases
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            under one board, and two bases under one board.</l>
                        <l n="22">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            And for the sides of the tabernacle westward you shall make
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            six boards.</l>
                        <l n="23">And you shall make two boards for the corners
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            of the tabernacle on the edges.</l>
                        <l n="24">And they shall be in one line
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            at the bottom, and they shall be integrated in one line at the top of it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            to one ring. It shall be so for the two of them; they shall be for the
                            two corners.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="25">And there shall be eight boards, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            their bases of silver, sixteen bases; two bases
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            under one board, and two bases under one board.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="26">And you shall make bars of acacia wood;
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            five for the boards of the one side of the tabernacle.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="27">And five bars for the boards of the second
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            side of the tabernacle at the edge westward.</l>
                        <l n="28">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            there shall be a middle bar in the midst of the boards that fills |the space|
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            from end to end.</l>
                        <l n="29">And you shall
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            overlay the boards with gold and you shall make their rings of gold
                            <milestone unit="page" n="130r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            for places for the bars, and you shall overlay them, <addSpan
                                spanTo="#add002" /><emph>the bars</emph><anchor xml:id="add002" />,
                            with gold.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="30">And you shall erect the tabernacle according to the manner
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            which you were shown in the mountain.</l>
                        <l n="31">And you shall make
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            a veil of blue and purple and scarlet silk and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            twined linen: he shall make of embroiderer’s work with cherubim.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="32">And you shall place it on four pillars of acacia
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            wood overlaid with gold, their hooks shall be of gold,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            on the four bases of silver.</l>
                        <l n="33">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            you shall place the veil under the hooks. And you shall bring
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            the law there, inside the veil, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the veil shall divide for you between the Holy and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            the Holy of Holies.</l>
                        <l n="34">And you shall put the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            cover on the ark of the law in the Holy
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            of Holies.</l>
                        <l n="35">And you shall set the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            table outside the veil, and the lampstand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            opposite the table on the side of the tabernacle toward the south,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            and you shall put the table on the north side.</l>
                        <l n="36">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            And you shall make a cover for the door of the tent, of blue and purple
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            and scarlet silk and twined linen of embroiderer’s work.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="37">And you shall make five pillars of acacia wood for the cover,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and overlay them with gold, their hooks shall be of gold, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="130v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-1-1" n="1" next="ADub.III.73.002.027.trl.xml#line-1-2" />
                            you shall cast five sockets of bronze for them.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
